name: IconSetConditionalFormat
description: Represents an IconSet criteria for conditional formatting.

properties.name: reverseIconOrder
properties.description: If true, reverses the icon orders for the IconSet. Note that this cannot be set if custom icons are used.

properties.name: showIconOnly
properties.description: If true, hides the values and only shows icons.

properties.name: style
properties.description: If set, displays the IconSet option for the conditional format.

properties.name: criteria
properties.description: An array of Criteria and IconSets for the rules and potential custom icons for conditional icons. Note that for the first criterion only the custom icon can be modified, while type, formula, and operator will be ignored when set.
